Should I be thinking about the alternatives I have because of this is getting a high risk for me ? I can't imagine how dramatic it would have been if this had happened during the Christmas season. 11/11

As an entrepreneur, I wear multiple hats and I always have a lot to do. I don't really have time and energy to spend on false-positives. Shopify is supposed to help me and my shop but right now it is painful. 10/11

I have no guarantee than the next person I do business with won't be affected too. I don't have that ban list for obvious reasons. I also have no guarantee that I won't get any trouble in future because one of your automated process has flagged my shop again. 9/10

Again, no other option than complying and no really human interaction here. I am pretty sure that you have at least 2 cellphones and 2 personal emails to warn us about the problem. There are an incredible amount of people on @Upwork, are you going to ask ID for all of them ? 7/11

Again that is a false-positive, this person is not working with me, the account is deactivated. This kind of actions, only based on a first-name, last-name, email is, in my opinion, terrifying. And can be easily bypassed (who trust user input ?) 6/11

This time, you left a 1 day notice to provide you ID of someone I haven't started to work with, and not in my current Timezone.
On top of that you will suspend the whole shop (cut it from the web) if I don't provide such documents within 2 days. 5/11

Basically all my operations are frozen : I can't see, fulfill or track orders. The whole admin dashboard and API is suspended. This time, the claim is that I have a _deactivated_ staff account name matching some government ban list. 4/11

This is not a top seller product, still the action was to hold money from all sales on the entire shop. And it was done without any notice, simply an email stating it was now locked. No other option than complying.
Today, I got completely locked out of my shop.  3/11

The first time, you suspended payouts claiming one of the product on the store was containing illegal ingredient (cannabis). My shop has 200+ variants, only a couple are actually Hemp oil, which Latin name match the forbidden ingredient. 2/11

Hey @Shopify @ShopifySupport, could you please stop bullying your small business customers?
Again, you've unilateraly taken greatly impacting decisions on my shop because of false-positives in your automation. Involving human before locking down the whole shop could be great 1/11
